OL,3,CMinister says 'unacceptable' to
OL,4,Coverrule Mandelson vetting
OL,6,FMr Jones also said the vetting papers
OL,7,Fcould be released to Parliament under
OL,8,Fthe terms of the motion passed by MPs
OL,9,Fdemanding access to the files relating
OL,10,Fto Lord Mandelson's appointment.
OL,12,FHe said "we're not far off" releasing
OL,13,Fthe second batch of files and when the
OL,14,Finformation emerged that UK Security
OL,15,FVetting had recommended against his
OL,16,Fappointment "legal advice was taken
OL,17,Fabout being able to include that in
OL,18,Fthe humble address, and we intend to
OL,19,Fdo so once it's gone through the Met
OL,20,FPolice and the Intelligence and
OL,21,FSecurity Committee".
OL,26,@tD@IOUtD@[O]xD@MOU}D@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
